    Therefore, $r_M(V(C)) = |V(C)| - 1$.
    Since $C$ was arbitrary, this is true for all components of $G$.
    Therefore, $G$ has a matching avoiding exactly one vertex from each of its components.
  \end{enumerate}
\end{proof}-/

